ent findings:`, `Open questions:`, `Plan:`, and `Cross-level notes:`.\nWhen calling `python`, emit exactly the tool-call format shown elsewhere in this prompt for this model. Use only that format; do not add markdown fences, prose wrappers, or alternate tool-call syntax. Do not quote or place tool-call markup inside explanatory text; when you decide to call the tool, emit the tool call itself.\nIf you use MOUSE, include integer row and col arguments.\nEFFICIENCY BUDGET \u2014 your score on each level is (baseline_actions / your_actions)^2, so every wasted action costs you quadratically.\nLevel 2: you have used 118 actions; a strong score needs about 58 or fewer. You are 2.0x over the target.\nIf you are not steadily making progress toward the level goal, commit to your single best hypothesis and the shortest sequence that tests it \u2014 do not exhaustively scan rows/columns or enumerate every option. Test one idea, read the result, then decide.", "kind": "tool", "inContext": true}, {"label": "THINKING", "content": "Interesting! The blue ended up at (16,24)-(19,43), which is 16 cols wide (43-24=19, so 20 cols? No, 43-24=19, so 20 cols). Wait, let me recount: 24, 25, ..., 43 is 20 cols. So the blue expanded from 12 cols to 20 cols!\nAlso, there's only ONE red block now at (16,8)-(19,19). The second red block at (16,28)-(19,39) is GONE!\nSo what happened:\n1. I tried UP, RIGHT, RIGHT, SPACE (but the executed actions were UP, RIGHT, UP - the batch was interrupted).\n2. The blue moved from (20,20)-(23,39) to (16,24)-(19,43).\n3. The blue expanded from 12 cols to 20 cols.\n4. The second red block disappeared.\nThis is very strange. The blue expanded when it moved away from the red block? Or when it moved to a position where it's not adjacent to any red block?\nLooking at the image, the blue is now at (16,24)-(19,43), which is 20 cols wide. The red block is at (16,8)-(19,19), which is 12 cols wide. The blue's left edge at 24 is 5 cols right of the red's right edge at 19. 